# Force Vercel's Python builder to install from requirements.txt (a plain
# `pip install -r`, no project self-build) instead of the uv manifests. When
# both a pyproject.toml and requirements.txt are present, Vercel prefers
# pyproject.toml/uv.lock and would try to `uv sync` the project — which this
# repo intentionally never installs (the Docker build uses
# `--no-install-project` and puts src/ on PYTHONPATH; pyproject has no
# [build-system]). Excluding them from the upload keeps the deploy predictable
# and keeps uvicorn's extras out of the function bundle. Local dev/Docker/uv are
# unaffected — these files stay in the repo, they just aren't uploaded to Vercel.
pyproject.toml
uv.lock
